Vite Overview: Modern frontend development tool (dev server + build tool) designed for speed.
Supported Frameworks: React, Vue, Svelte, TypeScript, and Vanilla JS.
Development Mode:
Serves only the files your project imports (on-demand compilation).
(imagine u have 100 js file , only 5 are useful , vite uses thouse 5 files only and send only those files to the broswer) 
Provides Hot Module Replacement (HMR) → where when u update only ine file no need of reoading the whole pages 
Production Mode:
Uses Rollup to make files optimized .
Optimizes code for performance, tree-shaking(Tree-shaking will cut out the code you never use so the final bundle is smaller and faster.), and caching.
Setup with React:
Command: npm create vite@latest → select React template → project ready.
JSX and modern JavaScript supported out-of-the-box.
Advantages over traditional bundlers:
Much faster development server (no slow full bundling).
Immediate feedback on changes → better productivity.
Simpler configuration, less setup time.
Use Cases:
Large React or Vue projects with many components.
Projects where fast hot reload is critical.
Modern JS / TypeScript applications.
Why Vite was created:
Traditional bundlers like Webpack were slow for large projects.
Needed a tool to make development faster and simpler.
My current Vite skills:
Can create and run a Vite + React project.
Understand dev server vs production build workflow.
Able to push projects to GitHub and explain why Vite is faster.
